                                <layout>The ogham inscription reads horizontally left-to-right and <q>is awkwardly placed near the edge of the stone</q> (West 2011). Occupying the centre of the stone above the ogham inscription is a two-line inscription in Norse runes which also reads left-to-right horizontally.</layout>
